C:\Data\Nucleus_Dev\Vostok_ACU_A\source\XCategory\Application\acu\Estimator\Estimator.c
      1          /**
      2           * @file
      3           * @brief       Estimates the time remaining in all the appliance compartments.
      4           *
      5           * @details     The Estimator module steps through all appliance compartments. For each
      6           *              compartment, it estimates the remaining time for the selected or running cycle.
      7           *              The Estimator uses the Interpreter to determine which cycle is selected and
      8           *              the current step executing in the cycle.
      9           *
     10           *              The Estimator uses time entries to predict cycle times. Time entries are assigned
     11           *              to phases. The time is only counted in the estimate if the following conditions
     12           *              are satisfied:
     13           *                  - The phase has a time assigned to it.
     14           *                  - At least one statement with an N-Flag set is predicted to execute.
     15           *              The Estimator predicts the execution path by evaluating Jump If process and Set
     16           *              State process statements.
     17           *
     18           *              If the estimated time calculation is taking too long, or if the predicted time is
     19           *              growing too large, then the Estimator will just use the MAXIMUM_ESTIMATED_SECONDS
     20           *              value as the time estimation for the compartment.
     21           *
     22           *              The estimation of each cycle is done in two parts. The first part is based on
     23           *              the most recently encountered time entry. The second part is based on the time
     24           *              entries for the rest of the cycle. The total time estimate is the sum of these two
     25           *              parts.
     26           *
     27           *              While a cycle is running, the Supervisor calls the Estimator__Countdown() function
     28           *              to update the estimated remaining time for the compartment. The Estimator will
     29           *              count down seconds until the time in the first part of the estimate has been
     30           *              consumed.
     31           *
     32           * @copyright   Copyright 2016-2017 Whirlpool Corporation.  All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL.
     33           */
     34          
